{"questionId":"7649","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>There is a proposal to place a satellite in orbit around planet Mars.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The ratio&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{distance of Mars from the Sun}}}}{{{\\text{distance of Earth from the Sun}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>distance of Mars from the Sun</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>distance of Earth from the Sun</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> = 1.5.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that the intensity of solar radiation at the orbit of Mars is about 600 W m<sup>–2</sup>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>use of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"I \\propto \\frac{1}{{{r^2}}}\">\n  <mi>I</mi>\n  <mo>∝</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>r</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;«1.36 × 10<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;× <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{{{{1.5}^2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>1.5</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>» ✔</p>\n<p>604 «W m<sup>–2</sup>» ✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"7649","referenceCode":"18N.2.HL.TZ0.8c.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Show that the intensity of solar radiation at the orbit of Mars is about 600 W m–2.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 8: Energy production","8.2 – Thermal energy transfer","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.3 – Wave charact